10/01/2005
BUCHAREST, Romania -- President Traian Basescu declared on Saturday (8 January) that Romania should increase its role in regional stabilisation processes for the sake of its own national security as well as to meet NATO and EU responsibilities. 
Basescu's comments came during a meeting with a delegation from the US Congress. 
They also discussed the strategic importance of the Black Sea region.
In other news, Romania's new government announced on Friday that it would appoint ethnic Hungarians as governors of three provinces with significant Magyar populations. 
Prime Minister Calin Tariceanu said they would head the local governments in Covasna, Bistrita Nasaud and Maramures, adding that the appointments reflect a changed attitude towards minorities. 
(Rompres - 08/01/05; AFP - 07/01/05)
